latestPosts.caption:
I know a jumpsuit hate to see me coming 😂

Styling a jumpsuit is easy because it’s a one-and-done outfit—here’s why:

1. Built-In Coordination

You don’t have to match a top and bottom—it’s already a complete look. Saving you time!

2. Versatile for Any Occasion

With the right shoes and accessories, a jumpsuit can be:
	•	Casual (with sneakers or sandals)
	•	Evening-ready (with bold jewelry and a clutch)

3. Flattering Silhouette

Most jumpsuits are designed to elongate the body and accentuate the waist, making them flattering on many body types.

4. Easy to Layer

They work well with jackets, blazers, cardigans, or even turtlenecks underneath in cooler seasons.

5. Minimal Accessories Needed

Because a jumpsuit is such a statement piece, you usually only need one or two accessories to finish the look.

Happy Styling babes!

Utility jumpsuit & mesh pumps @zara (old)
Clutch @jacquemus

My first time traveling on the Amtrak from CT TO NYC & NJ was seamless! Here’s what you should know to make your journey smooth and enjoyable on @amtrak .

1. Booking & Savings Tips
Advance Reservations: Book early to secure the best fares and seat options.
Discounts: Amtrak offers discounts for seniors, students, and more.
Amtrak Guest Rewards: Join this program to earn points for free trips and other benefits. ￼

2. Baggage & Packing
Carry-On Allowance: Each passenger can bring two personal items and two carry-on bags.

3. Essentials: Pack snacks, water, entertainment, a travel pillow, blanket, and toiletries. ￼ ￼

I recommend arriving at least 20-30 minutes before departure; 45 - 60 minutes if checking bags.

Safe travel babes!🚊
